    <label>PCI-DSS Network Security</label>
    <protected>false</protected>
    <values>
        <field>Framework__c</field>
        <value xsi:type="xsd:string">PCI_DSS</value>
    </values>
    <values>
        <field>Policy_Description__c</field>
        <value xsi:type="xsd:string">PCI-DSS Requirement 1 requires organizations to build and maintain secure network systems. Network access to cardholder data must be restricted, and all network connections must be monitored and logged.</value>
    </values>
    <values>
        <field>Legal_Citation__c</field>
        <value xsi:type="xsd:string">PCI-DSS Requirement 1 - Build and maintain a secure network</value>
    </values>
    <values>
        <field>Remediation_Steps__c</field>
        <value xsi:type="xsd:string">1. Configure IP restrictions for API access to cardholder data.
2. Enable Event Monitoring for all API access to sensitive objects.
3. Implement session timeout policies (15 minutes maximum).
4. Require multi-factor authentication for all users with cardholder data access.
5. Review network access logs monthly for unauthorized access attempts.</value>
    </values>
